52:46.580 --> 52:48.580
levels of hormones, levels of trans mirrors,

52:48.580 --> 52:49.740
all of that stuff.

52:49.740 --> 52:52.660
But it falls under the umbrella of affect.

52:52.660 --> 52:57.500
Affect essentially sets the stage for particular emotions

52:57.500 --> 53:00.300
to be more likely or less likely to emerge.

53:00.300 --> 53:02.860
So emotion and affect aren't the same thing.

53:02.860 --> 53:04.620
Affect is a bit more general.

53:04.620 --> 53:07.180
It sort of undergirds the possibility

53:07.180 --> 53:09.540
of having certain moods like feeling elated,

53:09.540 --> 53:12.540
happy or sad or depressed.

53:12.540 --> 53:14.380
It really sets the general stage

53:14.380 --> 53:17.220
for different types of specific emotions,

53:17.220 --> 53:19.380
even highly specific emotions.

53:19.380 --> 53:22.980
So in that way, when you're taking care of the big six,

53:22.980 --> 53:26.380
when you're tending to these six pillars on a regular basis,

53:26.380 --> 53:28.780
and I should point out that we really want to tend

53:28.780 --> 53:31.060
to those six pillars every single day

53:31.060 --> 53:33.300
or every single 24 hours,

53:33.300 --> 53:35.820
we really need to make those a regular investment

53:35.820 --> 53:37.940
to the extent that we can.

53:37.940 --> 53:41.180
When we do that, we create a neurochemical

53:41.180 --> 53:44.500
and a neural milieu that allows the brain

53:44.500 --> 53:47.180
to be in a better predictive state.

53:47.180 --> 53:51.220
It allows the brain to give rise to certain affects,

53:51.220 --> 53:54.380
spelled A-F-F-E-C-T-S,

53:54.380 --> 53:57.340
so affects that lead to certain emotions

53:57.340 --> 54:00.260
being more or less likely to occur.

54:00.260 --> 54:03.020
Put very simply, when we're tending to those six pillars

54:03.020 --> 54:06.420
on a regular basis, we feel better more generally,

54:06.420 --> 54:10.060
and therefore the emotions that we tend to have

54:10.060 --> 54:11.060
under different conditions,

54:11.060 --> 54:13.260
even conditions of a difficult interaction

54:13.260 --> 54:15.460
with a coworker or with a family member,

54:15.460 --> 54:18.420
tend to be more positive than if we are not tending

54:18.420 --> 54:19.900
to those six pillars.

54:19.900 --> 54:22.580
Now, in some sense, that's sort of a duh statement.

54:22.580 --> 54:24.020
For instance, if you're sleep deprived,

54:24.020 --> 54:25.740
if you're not fed well,

54:25.740 --> 54:27.340
like you haven't eaten in a few hours,

54:27.340 --> 54:29.460
of course, you're going to be more irritable,

54:29.460 --> 54:30.740
you're going to be more reactive,

54:30.740 --> 54:33.460
you are going to be more emotionally labile.

54:33.460 --> 54:34.620
But sleep and nutrition

54:34.620 --> 54:37.180
are just two of those six core pillars.

54:37.180 --> 54:38.900
When we talk about those core pillars

54:38.900 --> 54:40.900
and the necessity for tending to them

54:40.900 --> 54:43.540
on a regular, every 24-hour basis,

54:43.540 --> 54:44.980
what we're really talking about

54:44.980 --> 54:47.500
is creating a milieu within our brain and nervous system

54:47.500 --> 54:50.500
that allows the nervous system to do what it does best,

54:50.500 --> 54:53.500
and in fact, what its main job is to do,

54:53.500 --> 54:55.620
which is to predict what's going to happen next.

54:55.620 --> 54:57.900
Because as Lisa Feldman Barrett pointed out,

54:57.900 --> 55:01.180
emotions are really context-dependent states

55:01.180 --> 55:05.220
that allow us to navigate not just our present circumstances,

55:05.220 --> 55:08.580
but they are our nervous system and brain's best guess

55:08.580 --> 55:12.300
about the circumstances that we are soon going to encounter.

55:12.300 --> 55:13.740
Now, I don't offer you all of that

55:13.740 --> 55:17.460
as kind of a bunch of a tangled mess of nerd speak

55:17.460 --> 55:18.300
to confuse you.

55:18.300 --> 55:21.140
What I'm saying is that by tending to those six core pillars,

55:21.140 --> 55:25.340
you are shifting the likely affects that you will experience

55:25.340 --> 55:27.980
and therefore the likely emotions that you will experience.

55:27.980 --> 55:29.540
So you're biasing your whole system

55:29.540 --> 55:33.420
towards more positive affect and more positive emotions,

55:33.420 --> 55:36.540
regardless of what your life circumstances happen to be

55:36.540 --> 55:38.500
and the stressors that you encounter.

55:38.500 --> 55:40.300
And indeed, you also are including

55:40.300 --> 55:42.700
that six pillar of stress control.

55:42.700 --> 55:44.540
So when those stressors arrive,

55:44.540 --> 55:47.100
you'll be better able to navigate them.

55:47.100 --> 55:49.380
Now, this view of emotion regulation,

55:49.380 --> 55:51.020
of mood and mental health,

55:51.060 --> 55:53.220
is certainly not a novel concept.

55:53.220 --> 55:55.820
People have talked about the physiological regulation of mood

55:55.820 --> 55:58.540
from the time of William James and even earlier.

55:58.540 --> 56:00.420
It's been a long-standing question, for instance,

56:00.420 --> 56:02.700
or debate in psychology and philosophy.

56:02.700 --> 56:06.140
Do we feel anxiety in our body and then label it as anxiety,

56:06.140 --> 56:09.620
or do we feel anxiety in our mind and then our body follows?

56:09.620 --> 56:10.900
That's been a long-standing debate

56:10.900 --> 56:13.380
and frankly, there's evidence on both sides,

56:13.380 --> 56:14.700
which leads me to the conclusion,

56:14.700 --> 56:16.700
I think most neurobiologists and psychologists

56:16.700 --> 56:19.220
to the conclusion that those things are interrelated

56:19.220 --> 56:22.020
in a way that we can't really dissociate them completely

56:22.020 --> 56:23.340
at any level, right?

56:23.340 --> 56:24.340
When your heart rate goes up

56:24.340 --> 56:26.140
and you start breathing faster,

56:26.140 --> 56:27.580
if I were to induce that state in you,

56:27.580 --> 56:30.620
you'd probably interpret that as feeling anxious.

56:30.620 --> 56:31.460
In addition to that,

56:31.460 --> 56:32.980
something can make you anxious

56:32.980 --> 56:34.740
before your heart rate and breathing increases

56:34.740 --> 56:36.180
and then your heart rate and breathing increases.

56:36.180 --> 56:38.340
So no need to tease those apart.

56:38.340 --> 56:40.140
But if you think about the brain,

56:40.140 --> 56:42.100
in large part as a prediction machine

56:42.100 --> 56:44.660
and your brain as a metabolic regulator,

56:44.660 --> 56:47.180
it's trying to decide which organs need resources.

56:47.180 --> 56:49.820
How much resource can I dedicate to thinking,

56:49.820 --> 56:53.300
to creativity, to enjoying social interaction,

56:53.300 --> 56:55.260
to paying attention to what somebody else is saying

56:55.260 --> 56:57.340
as opposed to what's going on inside my body?

56:57.340 --> 56:59.140
All of those major functions of the brain

56:59.140 --> 57:01.820
as they relate to affect and emotions

57:01.820 --> 57:03.940
are going to be best supported,

57:03.940 --> 57:06.900
that is biased toward positive mood,

57:06.900 --> 57:10.060
positive affect, positive emotions,

57:10.060 --> 57:13.300
and therefore positive mental health outcomes

57:13.300 --> 57:15.580
when we're tending to those six pillars.

57:15.580 --> 57:17.940
Dr. Lisa Feldman Barrett referred to that whole process

57:17.940 --> 57:21.180
as the brain regulating a brain body budget.

57:21.180 --> 57:23.060
And she had beautiful analogies for that budget.

57:23.060 --> 57:24.860
And that's what led to the description

57:24.860 --> 57:27.940
of social interactions as either generating savings

57:27.940 --> 57:31.300
or being neutral or generating a taxed feeling,

57:31.300 --> 57:33.140
literally taxing that brain body budget.

57:33.140 --> 57:34.100
And I love that concept.

57:34.100 --> 57:35.700
And it's one that you can keep in mind.

57:35.700 --> 57:38.620
And indeed we can inject a lot of specificity

57:38.620 --> 57:41.780
into this whole process of improving mood and mental health

57:41.780 --> 57:43.380
through specific protocols.

57:43.380 --> 57:44.820
If you simply remember,

57:44.820 --> 57:49.140
if you make a daily investment in the six core pillars,

57:49.140 --> 57:51.860
you are building up that brain body budget.

57:51.860 --> 57:55.740
You will have more energetic resources to spend

57:55.740 --> 57:58.620
on whatever life circumstances come your way.

57:58.620 --> 58:01.500
Now, before we move into a discussion about protocols

58:01.500 --> 58:03.940
for how to better understand your life narrative

58:03.940 --> 58:06.700
to enhance your sense of self and confidence

58:06.700 --> 58:08.620
and things of that theme,

58:08.620 --> 58:11.300
I briefly want to mention that,

58:11.300 --> 58:13.940
of course there are known tools out there

58:13.940 --> 58:16.460
in the medical community and psychological community

58:16.460 --> 58:18.700
for improving mood and mental health.

58:18.700 --> 58:21.980
And while there are a variety of tools,

58:21.980 --> 58:24.940
one of the main tools of the psychiatrist

58:24.940 --> 58:26.780
is prescription drugs

58:26.780 --> 58:29.700
that target specific neuromodulator systems

58:29.700 --> 58:30.540
in the brain and body.

58:30.540 --> 58:32.580
For instance, SSRI,

58:32.580 --> 58:35.100
selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors

58:35.100 --> 58:37.820
or atypical antidepressants

58:37.820 --> 58:40.620
that target the dopamine and epinephrine systems

58:40.620 --> 58:42.660
such as wellbutrin, bupryorone

58:42.660 --> 58:44.580
or other types of antidepressants.

58:44.580 --> 58:48.460
Or for instance, nowadays there's a lot of growing excitement

58:48.460 --> 58:52.660
about clinical trials using relatively high dosages

58:52.660 --> 58:55.580
of psilocybin, which by the way,

58:55.580 --> 58:58.860
closely mimics the chemical serotonin.

58:58.860 --> 58:59.940
That's right, psilocybin,

58:59.940 --> 59:03.060
which is converted to psilocin in the brain.

59:03.060 --> 59:04.260
If you look at it chemically,

59:04.260 --> 59:06.180
it looks very much like serotonin

59:06.180 --> 59:08.420
although it has distinct effects from serotonin.

59:08.420 --> 59:09.620
I talked about psilocybin

59:09.620 --> 59:11.860
and what's being done in terms of the clinical trials,

59:11.860 --> 59:13.660
safety considerations.

59:13.660 --> 59:15.860
I talked about the potential hazard considerations

59:15.860 --> 59:17.940
and where the legality and all of that is going

59:17.940 --> 59:20.220
in that episode if you want to check that out.

59:20.220 --> 59:22.820
But the reason I'm taking a moment to mention these drugs,

59:22.820 --> 59:26.060
things like SSRIs, Prozax, Olav, Citalopram,

59:26.060 --> 59:29.060
wellbutrin, psilocybin and so on

59:29.060 --> 59:33.180
is that all of them target specific neuromodulator systems

59:33.180 --> 59:34.580
in the brain and body.

59:34.580 --> 59:37.980
And at the same time, it's fairly clear

59:38.020 --> 59:40.980
that mood disorders such as major depression

59:40.980 --> 59:43.420
are not necessarily deficits

59:43.420 --> 59:45.180
in things like serotonin or dopamine.

59:45.180 --> 59:48.340
They can be, but most often they are not.

59:48.340 --> 59:52.220
So why are such drugs prescribed for mood disorders

59:52.220 --> 59:53.380
and for mental health disorders?

59:53.380 --> 59:55.860
Well, because if specific neuromodulators

59:55.860 --> 59:58.420
like serotonin, dopamine or epinephrine

59:58.420 --> 01:00:01.900
are dramatically increased above baseline,

01:00:01.900 --> 01:00:05.220
that affords the brain the ability to rewire itself.

01:00:05.220 --> 01:00:08.060
Really the way to think about SSRIs

01:00:08.060 --> 01:00:11.300
or atypical antidepressants or psilocybin

01:00:11.300 --> 01:00:13.060
for the treatment of major depression

01:00:14.020 --> 01:00:18.300
is really to think about them as chemical tools

01:00:18.300 --> 01:00:21.260
to open or access neuroplasticity.

01:00:21.260 --> 01:00:23.060
And that's why it's oh so important

01:00:23.060 --> 01:00:25.500
that those drugs be combined with talk therapy

01:00:25.500 --> 01:00:28.020
where people are actively working through the sources,

01:00:28.020 --> 01:00:30.380
the real life sources and the historical sources,

01:00:30.380 --> 01:00:33.460
maybe even the trauma-based sources of their depression.

01:00:33.460 --> 01:00:36.660
And I mention this because there's a lot of debate nowadays

01:00:36.660 --> 01:00:39.140
as to whether or not these drugs are useful,

01:00:39.140 --> 01:00:42.140
whether or not the side effect profiles justify their use,

01:00:42.140 --> 01:00:46.900
whether or not they are applicable to young populations.

01:00:46.900 --> 01:00:48.180
There's a lot of debate about this.

01:00:48.180 --> 01:00:51.220
And certainly in the case of the psychedelics,

01:00:51.220 --> 01:00:53.140
there's a lot, a lot of debate

01:00:53.140 --> 01:00:55.420
because this is a newly emerging area

01:00:55.420 --> 01:00:56.860
and there's still not a lot of data,

01:00:56.860 --> 01:01:00.060
although it's starting to increase over time.

01:01:00.060 --> 01:01:03.460
But the key point here is that all of these drugs

01:01:03.460 --> 01:01:06.420
have the potential to work in some people, not others.

01:01:06.420 --> 01:01:08.500
Some people, they simply don't work for

01:01:08.500 --> 01:01:12.380
and they cause more problems than solutions they solve,

01:01:12.380 --> 01:01:17.220
but they tend to work by increasing the propensity

01:01:17.220 --> 01:01:21.540
for neuroplasticity by changing the neuromodulator milieu

01:01:21.540 --> 01:01:22.420
in the brain.

01:01:22.420 --> 01:01:24.740
And this is an important point when thinking about tools

01:01:24.740 --> 01:01:26.860
for enhancing mood and mental health,

01:01:26.860 --> 01:01:28.700
that when we think about tools

01:01:28.700 --> 01:01:30.620
for enhancing mood and mental health.

01:01:31.460 --> 01:01:33.540
And next, of course, we're going to talk about the tools

01:01:33.540 --> 01:01:38.140
that are specifically designed to target a specific aspect

01:01:38.140 --> 01:01:41.100
of one's life story or concept of self.

01:01:41.100 --> 01:01:45.260
All of that is always operating on a backdrop of two things,

01:01:45.260 --> 01:01:48.860
that overall neurochemical milieu and autonomic function

01:01:48.860 --> 01:01:50.860
that the six pillars relate to and support

01:01:50.860 --> 01:01:52.340
if we're attending to those,

01:01:52.340 --> 01:01:54.420
but any improvement in mood and mental health

01:01:54.420 --> 01:01:57.020
that's going to be significant, it's going to be noticeable

01:01:57.020 --> 01:01:58.300
and it's going to be stable,

01:01:58.300 --> 01:02:00.260
it's going to be pervasive over time,

01:02:00.260 --> 01:02:03.380
is going to require that some degree of neuroplasticity,

01:02:03.380 --> 01:02:06.020
some degree of neural rewiring occur.

01:02:06.020 --> 01:02:07.180
So I'm not bringing up the topic

01:02:07.180 --> 01:02:09.380
of these particular drug tools to say that

01:02:09.380 --> 01:02:11.740
they are the best way to improve mood and mental health.

01:02:11.740 --> 01:02:12.820
I'm certainly not saying that.

01:02:12.820 --> 01:02:15.740
They are, but one way to potentially improve

01:02:15.740 --> 01:02:16.980
mood and mental health.

01:02:16.980 --> 01:02:18.420
And if they are going to work,

01:02:18.420 --> 01:02:21.540
they always work best when done in concert

01:02:21.540 --> 01:02:22.380
with talk therapy,

01:02:22.380 --> 01:02:23.860
because they are opening the opportunity

01:02:23.860 --> 01:02:24.820
for neuroplasticity,

01:02:24.820 --> 01:02:27.540
but then that neuroplasticity has to be directed

01:02:27.540 --> 01:02:29.540
toward a particular endpoint.

01:02:29.540 --> 01:02:31.900
There has to be specific work that's being done

01:02:31.900 --> 01:02:35.180
by the individual or ideally the individual

01:02:35.180 --> 01:02:39.380
with an expert trained clinically certified therapist

01:02:39.380 --> 01:02:43.380
or psychologist or psychiatrist in order to make sure

01:02:43.380 --> 01:02:45.700
that the neuroplastic changes that occur

01:02:45.700 --> 01:02:47.460
lead to longstanding improvements

01:02:47.460 --> 01:02:49.060
in mood and mental health over time.

01:02:49.060 --> 01:02:51.380
Indeed, the drugs that I just described

01:02:51.380 --> 01:02:55.460
were originally designed as tools to allow people

01:02:55.500 --> 01:02:57.820
to access changes within their brain

01:02:57.820 --> 01:03:00.140
that would then allow them to enhance mood

01:03:00.140 --> 01:03:02.220
and mental health, but not have to rely

01:03:02.220 --> 01:03:05.620
on the drugs themselves for improved mood and mental health.

01:03:05.620 --> 01:03:08.620
And along those lines, I'm sure some of you out there

01:03:08.620 --> 01:03:10.900
are thinking about the supplement-based

01:03:10.900 --> 01:03:12.300
or nutrition-based approaches

01:03:12.300 --> 01:03:14.020
to enhancing these neuromodulators.

01:03:14.020 --> 01:03:16.540
And indeed, while they don't have the same potency

01:03:16.540 --> 01:03:18.540
as things like Wellbutrin and SSRIs

01:03:18.540 --> 01:03:20.180
at increasing things like dopamine

01:03:20.180 --> 01:03:21.860
and serotonin respectively,

01:03:21.860 --> 01:03:23.260
there is a growing number of people out there

01:03:23.260 --> 01:03:25.940
that are relying on daily supplementation

01:03:25.940 --> 01:03:29.260
with anywhere from one to three grams of L-tyrosine,

01:03:29.260 --> 01:03:31.420
amino acid precursor to dopamine,

01:03:31.420 --> 01:03:36.180
combined with often 300 to 600 milligrams of alpha-GPC

01:03:36.180 --> 01:03:39.460
as a way to enhance dopamine and acetylcholine

01:03:39.460 --> 01:03:43.380
and to set the stage for elevated levels of neuroplasticity.

01:03:43.380 --> 01:03:45.420
But it's very important to point out

01:03:45.420 --> 01:03:47.620
that the amino acid precursors

01:03:47.620 --> 01:03:49.980
to the various neuromodulators like L-tyrosine,

01:03:49.980 --> 01:03:54.020
like L-tryptophan, so L-tyrosine precursor to dopamine,

01:03:54.020 --> 01:03:57.660
L-tryptophan precursor to serotonin, and so on,

01:03:57.660 --> 01:04:00.660
that those don't have the same degree of potency,

01:04:00.660 --> 01:04:03.180
that is ability to enhance those neuromodulators.

01:04:03.180 --> 01:04:06.260
And so the extent to which they enrich the possibility

01:04:06.260 --> 01:04:09.020
for neuroplasticity still remains somewhat obscure.

01:04:09.020 --> 01:04:11.620
There haven't been clinical trials on that yet,

01:04:11.620 --> 01:04:14.300
at least not clinical trials that I am aware of.

01:04:14.300 --> 01:04:16.340
So I mentioned all of that stuff about drugs,

01:04:16.340 --> 01:04:17.540
whether or not it's psychedelics

01:04:17.540 --> 01:04:19.380
or whether or not it's prescription antidepressants

01:04:19.380 --> 01:04:21.340
or whether or not people are using

01:04:21.340 --> 01:04:24.900
a supplement-based amino acid-based protocol

01:04:24.900 --> 01:04:27.620
for increasing certain neuromodulators.

01:04:27.620 --> 01:04:29.420
I feel it was important to mention all of that because,

01:04:29.420 --> 01:04:32.060
well, first of all, it's quite prominent out there,

01:04:32.060 --> 01:04:34.260
certainly in the case of prescription antidepressants,

01:04:34.260 --> 01:04:36.340
and there's growing prominence

01:04:36.340 --> 01:04:39.620
and use of relatively high dose psilocybin.

01:04:39.620 --> 01:04:43.380
Again, always done with support talk therapy.

01:04:43.380 --> 01:04:46.340
This is done in a legal setting.

01:04:46.340 --> 01:04:48.140
I said legal, not illegal,

01:04:48.140 --> 01:04:51.060
a legal setting with a board-certified therapist.

01:04:51.060 --> 01:04:53.340
This is being done on university campuses,

01:04:53.340 --> 01:04:54.620
within research labs.

01:04:54.620 --> 01:04:56.300
And of course, I acknowledge that there are people

01:04:56.300 --> 01:04:58.180
who are using these compounds

01:04:58.180 --> 01:04:59.700
outside the realm of the university

01:04:59.700 --> 01:05:01.260
clinical study environment.

01:05:01.260 --> 01:05:02.500
So I mentioned these chemicals,

01:05:02.500 --> 01:05:05.500
not because I'm pointing to them as the path

01:05:05.500 --> 01:05:07.700
to improved mood and mental health.

01:05:07.700 --> 01:05:09.500
They can be, but they aren't always,

01:05:09.500 --> 01:05:10.500
and as I mentioned before,

01:05:10.500 --> 01:05:12.300
they can sometimes cause problems

01:05:12.300 --> 01:05:14.540
that lead people to wish that they hadn't taken them

01:05:14.540 --> 01:05:16.740
or to decide to not take them any further,

01:05:16.740 --> 01:05:18.340
a decision that absolutely has to be made

01:05:18.340 --> 01:05:19.540
with a healthcare professional

01:05:19.540 --> 01:05:21.140
who's well certified to do that.

01:05:21.140 --> 01:05:22.900
But I'm mentioning these tools

01:05:22.900 --> 01:05:27.900
because I want you to understand if they work, why they work.

01:05:28.060 --> 01:05:30.220
And one key point that was really emphasized

01:05:30.220 --> 01:05:33.260
by Dr. Paul Conti, who, as I mentioned before,

01:05:33.260 --> 01:05:34.140
is a psychiatrist,

01:05:34.140 --> 01:05:35.980
so he uses pharmacology in his practice,

01:05:35.980 --> 01:05:39.260
although he uses other non-pharmacologic tools as well,

01:05:39.260 --> 01:05:42.460
is that these pharmacologic tools are never to be viewed

01:05:42.460 --> 01:05:45.460
as the be all end all of enhancing mood and mental health.

01:05:45.460 --> 01:05:48.860
They are but one path to improving mood and mental health

01:05:48.860 --> 01:05:51.300
and indeed should be viewed as a path

01:05:51.300 --> 01:05:54.260
to getting people who are otherwise unable to engage

01:05:54.260 --> 01:05:55.740
in those six core pillars,

01:05:55.740 --> 01:05:57.420
those first principles of mental health,

01:05:57.420 --> 01:05:59.980
to be able to do those things on a regular basis.

