01:08:24.460 --> 01:08:27.940
It's something that's referred to as emotional granularity.

01:08:27.940 --> 01:08:31.020
So while some of us move through life

01:08:31.020 --> 01:08:35.300
with a sort of what I call emojification of emotions,

01:08:35.300 --> 01:08:36.820
you know, you got your happy face, happy,

01:08:36.860 --> 01:08:40.540
your sad face, sad, you know, you're angry, depressed,

01:08:40.540 --> 01:08:44.340
anxious, you know, those are labels for emotional states,

01:08:44.340 --> 01:08:46.460
or you could think of them as affects or emotions.

01:08:46.460 --> 01:08:49.100
I think of them as emotions, but they're not very specific.

01:08:49.100 --> 01:08:50.580
They're pretty broad bins.

01:08:50.580 --> 01:08:53.900
We say sad or depressed or super depressed

01:08:53.900 --> 01:08:56.300
or super sad, anxious, panic.

01:08:56.300 --> 01:08:57.700
And when we think of that as nuance,

01:08:57.700 --> 01:08:59.660
but it's not very nuanced.

01:08:59.660 --> 01:09:02.140
And Lisa's laboratory and other laboratories

01:09:02.140 --> 01:09:04.300
have explored two things.

01:09:04.300 --> 01:09:06.260
First, if people are asked to or encouraged

01:09:06.260 --> 01:09:08.940
to put more granularity, more specificity

01:09:08.940 --> 01:09:10.460
on what they're feeling,

01:09:10.460 --> 01:09:13.100
then it seems that their levels of emotional processing

01:09:13.100 --> 01:09:14.420
are better overall.

01:09:14.420 --> 01:09:15.980
How does that translate to emotions?

01:09:15.980 --> 01:09:20.980
Well, it translates to better overall feelings of wellbeing

01:09:21.540 --> 01:09:26.540
when one is placing more specificity on positive emotions.

01:09:26.980 --> 01:09:29.220
And the flip side is also true.

01:09:29.220 --> 01:09:30.580
So this is important to know.

01:09:30.580 --> 01:09:34.180
If one places more specificity on negative emotions,

01:09:34.180 --> 01:09:37.620
it also can enhance one's kind of experience

01:09:37.620 --> 01:09:39.460
of those negative emotions.

01:09:39.460 --> 01:09:42.780
Now, that means that this is a two-sided blade, all right?

01:09:42.780 --> 01:09:44.380
This isn't always a good thing.

01:09:44.380 --> 01:09:46.100
And if one is thinking about protocols

01:09:46.100 --> 01:09:48.100
for improving mood and mental health,

01:09:48.100 --> 01:09:52.620
the data make very clear that adding more specificity

01:09:52.620 --> 01:09:55.540
to our positive emotions in terms of the language we use,

01:09:55.540 --> 01:09:58.060
but also just the depth with which we process

01:09:58.060 --> 01:10:00.060
and think about those positive experiences

01:10:00.060 --> 01:10:02.060
can be very beneficial for us.

01:10:02.060 --> 01:10:03.820
So there are two studies that I'd like to highlight

01:10:03.820 --> 01:10:05.100
that relate to this.

01:10:05.100 --> 01:10:07.460
The first is entitled Effective Self-Monitoring

01:10:07.460 --> 01:10:08.700
Through Experience Sampling

01:10:08.700 --> 01:10:12.420
on Emotion Differentiation in Depression.

01:10:12.420 --> 01:10:14.380
And the second study is entitled

01:10:14.380 --> 01:10:16.060
Emotional Granularity Increases

01:10:16.060 --> 01:10:18.860
with Intensive Ambulatory Assessment.

01:10:18.860 --> 01:10:22.420
Methodological and individual factors influence how much.

01:10:22.420 --> 01:10:24.140
Now, each of these studies focus

01:10:24.140 --> 01:10:25.140
on something slightly different.

01:10:25.140 --> 01:10:26.420
The first study was mainly focused

01:10:26.420 --> 01:10:28.180
on people who have depression,

01:10:28.180 --> 01:10:32.260
and they were cued several, if not many times per day,

01:10:32.260 --> 01:10:36.100
to just think about and report on their emotional state.

01:10:36.100 --> 01:10:38.340
And that was done in order to get people

01:10:38.340 --> 01:10:40.260
to place more granularity,

01:10:40.260 --> 01:10:42.020
more specificity on what they're feeling,

01:10:42.020 --> 01:10:44.460
but also simply to tap into how they're feeling

01:10:44.460 --> 01:10:46.540
on a more regular basis throughout the day.

01:10:46.540 --> 01:10:48.540
The second study, which is one that included

01:10:48.540 --> 01:10:50.980
Dr. Lisa Feldman-Behr as an author,

01:10:50.980 --> 01:10:53.180
was slightly different because it focused

01:10:53.180 --> 01:10:55.180
on non-depressed individuals,

01:10:55.180 --> 01:10:56.940
and it cued them to touch into their emotions

01:10:56.940 --> 01:10:58.020
more times per day,

01:10:58.020 --> 01:11:01.420
and it also included some physiological measurements.

01:11:01.420 --> 01:11:03.500
And one in particular that we're going to talk about

01:11:03.500 --> 01:11:04.580
in some detail.

01:11:04.580 --> 01:11:07.180
Now, I don't have time to go into all the details

01:11:07.180 --> 01:11:08.020
of these studies.

